 used as comparative parameters. This study gives fresh insight into the interaction between technical requirements, environmental resources and material implementation. It is the first scientific approach in studying the Himalayan earthen heritage in a wide scope and connecting material research and cultural heritage from various perspectives - in particular archaeology, architecture, research on materials and building techniques.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aAgriculture (General). 0aEngineering (General). Civil engineering (General). 0aMathematics. 7aTechnology & Engineering / Materials Science / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2020z978311069628808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE DG 2019 Englishz978311061685908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chem., Mat.Sc, Geosc 2019 Englishz978311061064208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Materials Sc, Geosc 2019z9783110606461oZDB-23-DPC0 cEPUBz97831105901110 cprintz978311058996240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110591330zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110591330zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110591330.jpg  a978-3-11-061064-2 EBOOK PACKAGE Phys